        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Crystal Mill</h2>
        <p>You can drive around to the other side of the Maroon Bells (approximately 1.5 hours one-way from Aspen) to visit the incredibly picturesque and remote <strong>Crystal Mill</strong>. In order to reach the mill you'll need a 4x4 vehicle, otherwise you'll need to hike a scenic but long 8.2 miles (13.2 km) round-trip along the Crystal River, starting from Lizard Lake to reach this wondrous sight.</p>
    </section>




